.TH man 1 "20 August 2021" "SIMPLE_SHELL"
.SH NAME
hsh - simple_shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh (does not support arguments)

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell project entails implementation of a simple shell that can be compiled and launched from the command line on Unix-like systems.

.SH OVERVIEW
The simple_shell project is a team project conducted by Simon Usiagwu and Christabel Anyango, students at Holberton School through the ALX programme.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns the error code given by the last completed command followed by either ctrl-d or exit with no status code.

.SH SYNTAX
simple_shell$ <command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...

$ <command> | ./hsh
.SS

.SS
EXAMPLE 1:
simple_shell$ /bin/ls
.SS
EXAMPLE 2:
simple_shell$ ls -l
.SS
EXAMPLE 3:
simple_shell$ cat textfile
.SS


.SS
EXAMPLE 4:
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS
.SS alias
- create or list an alias

.SS cd
- change directory

.SS env
- list the current environment variable

.SS exit
- exit from shell

.SS help
- display help for a builtin command

.SS history
- display the command history for the current shell session

.SS setenv
- set and environment variable

.SS unsetenv
- unset an environment variable

.SH BUGS
No known bugs

.SH AUTHORS
Simon Usiagwu, Christabel Anyango (crkomo@gmail.com)
